---
/**
 * /industries/dod-contractors/
 * DoD Contractors & Defense-Adjacent Firms Vertical Page
 * 
 * Purpose: Trust surface + conversion entry point for defense-adjacent firms
 * Conversion: Assessment-oriented CTA, professional register
 * Tone: Serious, sober, premium, commercially grounded
 * 
 * Governance:
 * - No CMMC/NIST compliance promises
 * - No deterministic "win more contracts" language
 * - No legacy DCS/PromptCore terminology
 * - No unverified stats or percentages
 * - No patriotic/militarized gimmicks
 * - CTA routes to /contact/
 * - Canonical offer: Digital Credibility Assessment
 * - Service mapping uses approved taxonomy only
 */

import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "Digital Credibility for DoD Contractors";
const pageDescription = "Compliance-aware website modernization for defense contractors and GovCon firms. Structured credibility, search readiness, and capability signaling for risk-averse evaluators.";
---

<BaseLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>

  <!-- 1. HERO -->
  <section class="hero hero--dod">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Digital Credibility for Defense-Adjacent Firms</h1>
      <p class="hero__subhead">
        Your website is a trust surface. Evaluators, partners, and primes 
        assess capability before the first conversation. We help defense-adjacent 
        firms build digital presence that signals capability and earns confidence.
      </p>
      <a 
        href="/contact/" 
        class="btn btn-primary"
        data-nt-event="dod_cta_assessment"
      >
        Request a Digital Credibility Assessment
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 2. WHY THIS MATTERS -->
  <section class="section section--why-matters">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why Digital Credibility Matters in Defense Contracting</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          The website for a defense-adjacent firm is not a brochure. It functions 
          as a trust surface, discovery surface, and capability-signaling layer. 
          Risk-averse evaluators—contracting officers, prime partners, teaming 
          leads—research your firm before engaging.
        </p>
        <p>
          Search and discovery readiness affects whether your capabilities surface 
          at all. Information hierarchy and presentation quality affect whether 
          evaluators perceive organizational maturity. Compliance-aware positioning 
          affects whether buyers feel confident proceeding.
        </p>
        <p>
          Most defense-adjacent firms under-invest in digital presence. The result: 
          under-signaled capability, invisible pipeline contribution, and 
          preventable friction in business development.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 3. COMMON DIGITAL GAPS -->
  <section class="section section--gaps">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Common Digital Gaps in Defense-Adjacent Firms</h2>
      <p class="section__intro">
        These patterns are not criticism—they reflect under-investment norms 
        across the sector. Addressing them creates differentiation.
      </p>
      
      <div class="gap-grid">
        
        <div class="gap-card">
          <h3>Under-Signaled Capability</h3>
          <p>
            Actual expertise exceeds what the website communicates. 
            Evaluators see a fraction of your real qualifications.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="gap-card">
          <h3>Invisible Compliance Posture</h3>
          <p>
            Security and compliance commitments exist but are not 
            visible to external evaluators assessing risk.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="gap-card">
          <h3>Unclear Information Hierarchy</h3>
          <p>
            Critical information is present but buried. Evaluators 
            must work to understand what you do and for whom.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="gap-card">
          <h3>No Measurement Layer</h3>
          <p>
            Pipeline contribution from digital presence is unmeasured. 
            Marketing and BD operate without visibility.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="gap-card">
          <h3>Poor Search Readiness</h3>
          <p>
            Contract-relevant capabilities do not surface in search. 
            Discovery depends entirely on existing relationships.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 4. WHAT NEXTARA IMPROVES -->
  <section class="section section--improvements">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What We Help You Improve</h2>
      <div class="improvement-grid">

        <div class="improvement-block">
          <h3>Structured Credibility Architecture</h3>
          <p>
            Information hierarchy, trust signaling, and presentation 
            quality aligned to buyer expectations in regulated environments.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="improvement-block">
          <h3>Capability Signaling</h3>
          <p>
            Your website should communicate the full scope of what you do, 
            who you serve, and why you're qualified—clearly and completely.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="improvement-block">
          <h3>Search &amp; Discovery Readiness</h3>
          <p>
            Technical and content optimization so contract-relevant 
            capabilities surface where evaluators research.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="improvement-block">
          <h3>Telemetry &amp; Measurement</h3>
          <p>
            A measurement layer that shows pipeline contribution, 
            engagement patterns, and conversion attribution.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 5. COMPLIANCE-AWARE CREDIBILITY BLOCK -->
  <section class="section section--compliance-aware">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Compliance-Aware Modernization</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          We do not provide compliance consulting, certification preparation, 
          or legal guidance. What we do provide: digital presence modernization 
          that accounts for the expectations of compliance-conscious buyers.
        </p>
        <p>
          This means structured presentation, appropriate trust signaling, 
          clear information hierarchy, and credibility architecture suitable 
          for risk-averse evaluators in regulated environments.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 6. SERVICE MAPPING -->
  <section class="section section--services">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Relevant Capabilities</h2>
      <p class="section__intro">
        Our work with defense-adjacent firms typically involves 
        these practice areas.
      </p>
      
      <div class="service-grid">

        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Growth Blocker Audit</h3>
          <p>
            Systematic identification of credibility gaps, conversion 
            friction, and structural weaknesses limiting digital performance.
          </p>
          <a href="/services/growth-blocker-audit/" class="service-card__link">
            Learn more →
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Tracking Governance</h3>
          <p>
            Measurement architecture that provides visibility into 
            pipeline contribution and engagement patterns.
          </p>
          <a href="/services/tracking-governance/" class="service-card__link">
            Learn more →
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>SEO &amp; Indexing</h3>
          <p>
            Technical and content optimization for search readiness—ensuring 
            contract-relevant capabilities surface in discovery.
          </p>
          <a href="/services/seo-indexing/" class="service-card__link">
            Learn more →
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Conversion Architecture</h3>
          <p>
            Structured pathways from discovery to engagement—designed for 
            professional buyer journeys, not consumer funnels.
          </p>
          <a href="/services/conversion-architecture/" class="service-card__link">
            Learn more →
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 7. PROCESS / ENGAGEMENT BLOCK -->
  <section class="section section--process">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>How We Work</h2>
      <div class="process-steps">

        <div class="process-step">
          <span class="process-step__number">1</span>
          <h3>Discovery</h3>
          <p>
            We learn about your firm, your buyers, and your 
            business development priorities.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="process-step">
          <span class="process-step__number">2</span>
          <h3>Assessment</h3>
          <p>
            A structured review of your current digital presence, 
            credibility gaps, and improvement opportunities.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="process-step">
          <span class="process-step__number">3</span>
          <h3>Roadmap</h3>
          <p>
            Prioritized recommendations with clear scope, 
            sequencing, and expected outcomes.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="process-step">
          <span class="process-step__number">4</span>
          <h3>Implementation</h3>
          <p>
            Execution against the roadmap—measured, 
            governed, and iteratively improved.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 8. FAQ -->
  <section class="section section--faq">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      
      <div class="faq-list">

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__question">
            Do you provide CMMC or compliance consulting?
          </summary>
          <div class="faq-item__answer">
            <p>
              No. We improve digital presence—websites, search readiness, 
              credibility architecture. We do not provide compliance certification, 
              audit preparation, or legal guidance. Our work is compliance-aware, 
              meaning we account for the expectations of buyers in regulated 
              environments, but we are not compliance consultants.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__question">
            How do you measure results?
          </summary>
          <div class="faq-item__answer">
            <p>
              We implement a telemetry layer that tracks engagement, conversion 
              events, and pipeline attribution. You gain visibility into what 
              your digital presence is actually contributing to business development.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__question">
            What's the typical engagement timeline?
          </summary>
          <div class="faq-item__answer">
            <p>
              Timeline depends on scope. The assessment phase clarifies what's 
              needed and produces a roadmap with realistic sequencing. Most 
              modernization engagements span weeks to months, not days.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__question">
            Do you work with classified programs?
          </summary>
          <div class="faq-item__answer">
            <p>
              We work on public-facing digital presence only. Our scope is 
              websites, search optimization, credibility architecture, and 
              marketing measurement—not classified systems or controlled 
              unclassified information.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__question">
            Can you guarantee we'll win more contracts?
          </summary>
          <div class="faq-item__answer">
            <p>
              No. We improve digital credibility, search readiness, and 
              measurement maturity. These improvements support business 
              development, but contract outcomes depend on many factors 
              beyond digital presence.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 9. CTA BLOCK -->
  <section class="section section--cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Start with a Digital Credibility Assessment</h2>
      <p>
        A structured review of your public-facing presence, search readiness, 
        and capability signaling. We'll identify gaps and provide a prioritized 
        roadmap for improvement.
      </p>
      <a 
        href="/contact/" 
        class="btn btn-primary"
        data-nt-event="dod_cta_assessment_close"
      >
        Request an Assessment
      </a>
      <p class="cta-secondary">
        <a href="/contact/">Or contact us with questions</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>